---
import ArticleLayout from "@/layouts/ArticleLayout.astro";
import { withBase } from "@/utils/site";
---

<ArticleLayout
  title="Start Here"
  description="An orientation for first-time visitors to Articulate, its repository, and its architectural journal."
  eyebrow="Orientation"
>
  <h2>What Articulate Is</h2>
  <p>
    Articulate is a production-oriented reference architecture for AI-native systems. It is also
    an architectural laboratory and a public engineering journal.
  </p>
  <p>
    The project exists to show how architectural reasoning emerges over time: the questions asked,
    assumptions made, trade-offs considered, evidence gathered, and changes introduced.
  </p>

  <h2>Product, Repository, and Journal</h2>
  <p>
    The working software is the product surface and the evidence. The repository is the canonical
    project record. The website is the narrative layer that helps readers move through that record.
  </p>

  <h2>What Episodes Are</h2>
  <p>
    Episodes are narrative investigations into architectural questions. An Episode may produce or
    revise principles and decisions, introduce patterns, document experiments, and point to
    repository assets.
  </p>

  <h2>How the Parts Relate</h2>
  <p>
    Principles provide long-lived architectural guidance. Decisions record commitments and their
    consequences. Patterns describe reusable architectural approaches that survive contact with
    implementation. Experiments keep uncertainty visible. Code, diagrams, and models provide evidence.
  </p>

  <h2>Suggested Routes</h2>
  <div class="route-grid">
    <article class="index-card">
      <h3>I want to understand the vision.</h3>
      <p>Start with the preface, the first two Episodes, and the About page.</p>
      <p><a href={withBase("/episodes/0001-why-articulate-exists/")}>Open Episode 0001</a></p>
    </article>
    <article class="index-card">
      <h3>I want to understand the guiding principles.</h3>
      <p>Use Principles to see the enduring guidance shaping architecture, decisions, and patterns.</p>
      <p><a href={withBase("/principles/")}>Open Principles</a></p>
    </article>
    <article class="index-card">
      <h3>I want to study the architecture.</h3>
      <p>Use the current architecture view to see what is known and what is not yet decided.</p>
      <p><a href={withBase("/architecture/")}>Open Architecture</a></p>
    </article>
    <article class="index-card">
      <h3>I want practical examples and patterns.</h3>
      <p>Use Patterns and Experiments as the implementation begins to produce reusable evidence.</p>
      <p><a href={withBase("/patterns/")}>Open Patterns</a></p>
    </article>
    <article class="index-card">
      <h3>I want to follow the evolution.</h3>
      <p>Use the evolution timeline and decision index to see how the architecture changes.</p>
      <p><a href={withBase("/evolution/")}>Open Evolution</a></p>
    </article>
  </div>
</ArticleLayout>
